The points in the partition will then be
formula_30

=== Left rule ===

For the left rule, the function is approximated by its values at the left endpoints of the subintervals. This gives multiple rectangles with base and height . Doing this for , and summing the resulting areas gives
formula_31

The left Riemann sum amounts to an overestimation if &quot;f&quot; is monotonically decreasing on this interval, and an underestimation if it is monotonically increasing.
The error of this formula will be 
formula_32
where formula_33 is the maximum value of the absolute value of formula_34 over the interval.

=== Right rule ===

For the right rule, the function is approximated by its values at the right endpoints of the subintervals. This gives multiple rectangles with base and height . Doing this for , and summing the resulting areas gives
formula_35

The right Riemann sum amounts to an underestimation if &quot;f&quot; is monotonically decreasing, and an overestimation if it is monotonically increasing.
The error of this formula will be 
formula_36
where formula_33 is the maximum value of the absolute value of formula_34 over the interval.

=== Midpoint rule ===

For the midpoint rule, the function is approximated by its values at the midpoints of the subintervals. This gives for the first subinterval, for the next one, and so on until . Summing the resulting areas gives
formula_39

The error of this formula will be
formula_40
where formula_41 is the maximum value of the absolute value of formula_42 over the interval. This error is half of that of the trapezoidal sum; as such the middle Riemann sum is the most accurate approach to the Riemann sum.
