<doc id="176518" wikidata="Q1786989" url="?curid=176518" title="Saint John County, New Brunswick">
<text>Saint John County (2016 population: 74,020) is located in southern New Brunswick, Canada. The city of Saint John dominates the county. Elsewhere in the county, tourism is focused around the Bay of Fundy.

