<doc id="176524" wikidata="Q1520380" url="?curid=176524" title="Victoria County, New Brunswick">
<text>Victoria County (2016 population 18,617) is located in northwestern New Brunswick, Canada. Farming, especially of potatoes, is the major industry in the county. The area was named for Queen Victoria.

